ulation_density_km2=auto\n| population_footnotes=<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n| population_est        = {{formatnum:88,800|R}}\n| pop_est_as_of=2015\n| pop_est_footnotes=<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.townplan.gov.my/epublisiti/drsnp2040/DRAF%20RS%20PERAK.pdf|title=Rancangan Struktur Negeri Perak 2040|format=PDF|page=316}}</ref>\n|timezone=[[Malaysian Standard Time|MST]]\n|utc_offset=+8\n|timezone_DST=Not observed\n| utc_offset_DST               = +8\n|postal_code_type=[[Postal codes in Malaysia|Postcode]]\n|postal_code=35000-35600\n|area_code=+6-05\n|area_code_type          = [[Telephone numbers in Malaysia|Calling code]]\n|registration_plate_type =[[Vehicle registration plates of Malaysia|Vehicle registration plates]]\n|registration_plate=A\n}}\n\nThe '''Batang Padang District''' ({{lang-ms|Daerah Batang Padang}}) is a [[List of districts in Malaysia|district]] in [[Perak]], [[Malaysia]]. This district is administered by a local councils, namely, the Tapah District Council, based in [[Tapah]]. The major towns of Batang Padang are [[Bidor]], [[Tapah]] and [[Sungkai]].\n\nIn August 2007 the Perak Government announced the discovery of large water aquifers at Batang Padang. They plan to sell the water to neighbouring [[Selangor]] to help solve future water shortage problems in that state.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utusan.com.my/berita/nasional/langkah-segera-atasi-banjir-di-batang-padang-1.32346|title=Langkah segera atasi banjir di Batang Padang|first=SAYED HESHAM|last=IDRIS|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe sub-district of Tanjung Malim was split from this district to pave the way for [[Muallim District]] which was officiated on 11 January 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bharian.com.my/node/113170 |title=Muallim rasmi menjadi daerah ke-11 di Perak |author=Shamsul Kamal Amarudin |publisher=Berita Harian |date=11 January 2016 |accessdate=2014-09-17}}</ref>\n\n==Administrative divisions==\n[[File:Map of Batang Padang District, Perak.svg|250px|thumb|Map of Batang Padang District]]\nBatang Padang District is divided into 4 [[mukim]]s, which are:<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://pdttapah.perak.gov.my/maklumat-korporat/pengenalan/senarai-mukim-dan-statistik-penduduk|title=Laman Web Pejabat Daerah Dan Tanah - Senarai Mukim Dan Statistik Penduduk|first=TAPAH|last=ADMIN|website=pdttapah.perak.gov.my|access-date=2017-12-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171211041805/http://pdttapah.perak.gov.my/maklumat-korporat/pengenalan/senarai-mukim-dan-statistik-penduduk|archive-date=2017-12-11|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* Batang Padang (Tapah town)\n* [[Bidor]]\n* [[Chenderiang]]\n* [[Sungkai]]\n\n== Federal Parliament and State Assembly Seats ==\nList of Batang Padang district representatives in the Federal Parliament ([[Dewan Rakyat]])\n<br />\n{| class=\"toccolours sortable\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; text-align: left;\"\n|-\n! align=\"center\"|Parliament !! Seat Name !! Member of Parliament !! Party\n|-\n! align=\"left\"|P72\n| [[Tapah (federal constituency)|Tapah]] || [[Saravanan Murugan|Saravanan A/L Murugan]]|| Perikatan Nasional (BN-MIC)\n|-\n! align=\"left\"|P77\n| [[Tanjong Malim (federal constituency)|Tanjong Malim]] || [[Chang Lih Kang]] || Pakatan Harapan (PKR)\n|-\n|}\n\n<br />\nList of Batang Padang district representatives in the State Legislative Assembly of Perak\n<br />\n{| class=\"toccolours sortable\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"3\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; text-align: left;\"\n|-\n! align=\"center\"|Parliament !! State !! Seat Name !! State Assemblyman !! Party\n|-\n! align=\"left\"|P72\n| N47 || [[Chenderiang (state constituency)|Chenderiang]] || [[Ahmad Faizal Azumu]] || Perikatan Nasional (PPBM)\n|-\n! align=\"left\"|P72\n| N48 || [[Ayer Kuning (state constituency)|Ayer Kuning]] || Samsudin Bin Abu Hassan || Perikatan Nasional (BN-UMNO)\n|-\n! align=\"left\"|P77\n| N57 || [[Sungkai (state constituency)|Sungkai]] || Sivanesan A/L Achalingam || Pakatan Harapan (DAP)\n|-\n! align=\"left\" |P77\n| N58 ||[[Slim (state constituency)|Slim]]|| Mohd Khusairi Abdul Talib || Perikatan Nasional (BN-UMNO)\n|-\n! align=\"left\" |P77\n| N59 ||[[Behrang (state constituency)|Behrang]]|| Aminuddin Zulkipli || Pakatan Harapan (AMANAH)\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n{{commons category|Batang Padang District}}\n* [[Districts of Malaysia]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Perak}}\n[[Category:Districts of Perak]]\n\n{{Districts of Malaysia}}\n{{Perak-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{for|the federal constituency formerly represented in the Dewan Rakyat|Batang Padang (federal constituency)}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n|name=Batang Padang District\n|official_name=Daerah Batang Padang\n|translit_lang1=Other\n|translit_lang1_type1=[[Simplified Chinese character|Chinese]]\n|translit_lang1_info1={{lang|zh-hans|\u9a6c\u767b\u5df4\u51b7\u53bf}}\n|translit_lang1_type2=[[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n|translit_lang1_info2={{lang|ta|\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd}}\n|settlement_type={{flagicon|Malaysia}} [[Districts of Malaysia|District]] of [[Malaysia]]\n|pushpin_map=Malaysia District\n| image_map               = Batang Padang highlighted in Perak, Malaysia.svg\n|map_caption=Location of '''Batang Padang District''' in [[Perak]]\n| coordinates             = {{coord|4|05|N|101|20|E|region:MY|display=title, inline}}\n|pushpin_label_position=Center\n|pushpin_map_caption=Location of '''Batang Padang District''' in [[Malaysia]]\n|image_flag                  = \n|subdivision_name={{MAS}}\n|subdivision_name1={{flag|Perak}}\n|subdivision_type=[[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_type1=[[States and federal territories of Malaysia|State]]\n|seat=[[Tapah]]\n|parts_type = Local area government(s)\n|parts = [[Tapah District Council]]\n|leader_title=District officer\n|leader_name=n/a<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pdttapah.perak.gov.my/maklumat-